FBIS4-2457 "drchi069_k_94008" FBIS-CHI-94-069 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Crackdown on Dissidents, Reporters Arrested Crackdown on Dissidents, Reporters Arrested Detained Dissidents Released HK1104012994 Hong Kong AFP in English 0113 GMT 11 Apr 94 HK1104012994 Hong Kong AFP English BFN [Text] Beijing, April 11 (AFP) -- The three Chinese dissidents detained Friday and Saturday during the visit of French Prime Minister Edouard Balladur were released Sunday, the dissidents said Monday. Bao Ge, Wang Fucheng and Yang Zhou were able to return home Sunday, but were placed under house arrest for most of the day and their telephones were cut until Monday morning so that they could not speak with the press, the dissidents said. They were released after the departure Sunday of Balladur from Shanghai, they added.
